<li id="cite_note-20"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20" title="">^</a></b> Elizabeth Marshall Thomas (2006)</li>
<li id="cite_note-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7358868.stm" class="external text" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7358868.stm" rel="nofollow">"Human line 'nearly split in two'"</a>. April 24, 2008<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7358868.stm" class="external free" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7358868.stm" rel="nofollow">http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7358868.stm</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Human+line+%27nearly+split+in+two%27&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=April+24%2C+2008&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F2%2Fhi%2Fscience%2Fnature%2F7358868.stm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Bushmen"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Vitrina_de_la_pol.C3.A9mica-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Vitrina_de_la_pol.C3.A9mica_22-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFY.C3.A1niz.2C_Juan_Pedro">Yániz, Juan Pedro. <a href="http://www.abc.es/hemeroteca/historico-06-01-2002/abc/Catalunya/vitrina-de-la-polemica_70155.html" class="external text" title="http://www.abc.es/hemeroteca/historico-06-01-2002/abc/Catalunya/vitrina-de-la-polemica_70155.html" rel="nofollow">"Vitrina de la polémica"</a> (in Spanish). <i><a href="/wiki/ABC_(newspaper)" title="ABC (newspaper)">ABC.es</a></i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.abc.es/hemeroteca/historico-06-01-2002/abc/Catalunya/vitrina-de-la-polemica_70155.html" class="external free" title="http://www.abc.es/hemeroteca/historico-06-01-2002/abc/Catalunya/vitrina-de-la-polemica_70155.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.abc.es/hemeroteca/historico-06-01-2002/abc/Catalunya/vitrina-de-la-polemica_70155.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-10-26</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Vitrina+de+la+pol%C3%A9mica&amp;rft.atitle=%5B%5BABC+%28newspaper%29%7CABC.es%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Y%C3%A1niz%2C+Juan+Pedro&amp;rft.au=Y%C3%A1niz%2C+Juan+Pedro&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.es%2Fhemeroteca%2Fhistorico-06-01-2002%2Fabc%2FCatalunya%2Fvitrina-de-la-polemica_70155.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Bushmen"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
<p>Tad Williams' epic "Otherland" series of novels features&#160;!Xabbu, a South African bushman and includes many references to their mythology and culture. He acknowledges that the character is highly fictionalised and apologises for any misrepresentation.</p>
